      "title": "3D ASCII Cube",
      "solution": "n = int(raw_input())\r\ngrid = [int(raw_input()) for i in range(n)]\r\n\r\nif not grid:\r\n    grid = ['   ']\r\nsize = pow(len(grid), 1.0/3.0)\r\nif str(size)[1:] == '.0':\r\n    size = round(size)\r\nsize = int(size)\r\ngrid_range = range(size)\r\ngrid_output = []\r\nk = 0\r\nfor j in grid_range:\r\n    row_top = ' ' * (size * 2 + 1) + '_' * (size * 4)\r\n    if j:\r\n        row_top = '|{}|{}|{}|'.format(row_top[:size * 2 - 1], '_' * (size * 2), '_' * (size * 2 - 1))\r\n    grid_output.append(row_top)\r\n    for i in grid_range:\r\n        row_display = '{}/{}'.format(' ' * (size * 2 - i * 2), ''.join(('{}{}{}/'.format('' if grid[k + x] > 9 or grid[k + x] < 0 else ' ', str(grid[k + x]).ljust(1), '' if grid[k + x] > 99 or grid[k + x] < -9  else ' ')) for x in grid_range))\r\n        row_bottom = '{}/{}'.format(' ' * (size * 2 - i * 2 - 1), '___/' * size)\r\n        if j != grid_range[-1]:\r\n            row_display += '{}|'.format(' ' * (i * 2))\r\n            row_bottom += '{}|'.format(' ' * (i * 2 + 1))\r\n        if j:\r\n            display_char = row_display[size * 4 + 1].strip()\r\n            row_display = '|{}{}{}'.format(row_display[1:size * 4 + 1], display_char if display_char else '|', row_display[size * 4 + 2:])\r\n            row_bottom = '|{}|{}'.format(row_bottom[1:size * 4 + 1], row_bottom[size * 4 + 2:])\r\n        k += size\r\n        grid_output += [row_display, row_bottom]\r\nfor i, x in enumerate(grid_output):\r\n    print x\r\n",
      "statement": "Draw a text representation of a 3D cube from a list of numbers.\n\nEach cell must be 1 line high and 3 characters wide, excluding any connectors.\nLines parallel to the X axis are represented by underscore:  {{_}} characters.\nLines parallel to the Y axis are represented by forward slash: {{/}} characters.\nLines parallel to the Z axis are represented by vertical bar: {{|}} characters.\n\nFormatting rules:\nThe integer should be centered if possible, or aligned to the left if not.\nIf the integer overlaps anything, the integer should be shown.",
