    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h1><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h1>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">Draw a text representation of a 3D cube from a list of numbers.<br><br>Each cell must be 1 line high and 3 characters wide, excluding any connectors.<br>Lines parallel to the X axis are represented by underscore:  <const>_</const> characters.<br>Lines parallel to the Y axis are represented by forward slash: <const>/</const> characters.<br>Lines parallel to the Z axis are represented by vertical bar: <const>|</const> characters.<br><br>Formatting rules:<br>The integer should be centered if possible, or aligned to the left if not.<br>If the integer overlaps anything, the integer should be shown.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1:</strong> The number <var>N</var> of integers going to be input.<br><strong>Next <var>N</var> lines:</strong> An Integer <var>I</var> which goes in the cube.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">Multiple lines with each line displaying a new row of the cube.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &le; <var>N</var> &le; 64<br>-99 &le; <var>I</var> &le; 999</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">8\n0\n1\n2\n3\n4\n5\n6\n7</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre c